### Step 1: Schema Migration

Create file: `schema/migrations/20260304_observation_coding_agent_fields.surql`

```sql
-- Add coding-agent-specific fields to observation table
-- and observed_in relation for session tracking.

BEGIN TRANSACTION;

-- New fields on observation for coding agent context
DEFINE FIELD observation_type ON observation TYPE option<string>
  ASSERT $value IN ["contradiction", "duplication", "missing", "deprecated", "pattern", "anomaly"] OR $value IS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD source_session ON observation TYPE option<record<agent_session>>;
DEFINE FIELD files ON observation TYPE option<array<string>>;
DEFINE FIELD code_snippet ON observation TYPE option<string>;

-- New field on agent_session for session-end summary
DEFINE FIELD observations_logged ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<observation>>>;

COMMIT TRANSACTION;

-- observed_in relation: observation -> agent_session
-- (DEFINE TABLE cannot be inside transaction with RELATION type in some SurrealDB versions)
DEFINE TABLE OVERWRITE observed_in TYPE RELATION IN observation OUT agent_session SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD added_at ON observed_in TYPE datetime;
```

Note: The `DEFINE TABLE ... TYPE RELATION` may need to be outside the transaction depending on SurrealDB v3.0 behavior. Follow the pattern from the existing migration at `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/schema/migrations/20260304_agent_session_and_subtask.surql` which defines relation tables inside a transaction (lines 33-45). If that works, keep it inside.

